Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.58,0:01:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在这世界上\N{\fs60}There are over 550 million firearms
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.16,0:01:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}全世界一共有5亿5千万支军火\N{\fs60}in world-wide circulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.36,0:01:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那就是说每12个人中就有1只枪\N{\fs60}That's one firearm for every twelve people on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.31,0:01:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}唯一的问题是\N{\fs60}The only question is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.91,0:01:26.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们如何让其他11个人也有枪\N{\fs60}how do we arm the other eleven?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.18,0:02:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,200)\fs120\pos(942,725.2)}战争{\bord0\shad4\fs90} 之 {\r\bord0\shad4\fs120}王
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.05,0:04:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不用担心\N{\fs60}You don't have to worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.02,0:04:40.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不会说一堆谎话 让你觉得我是好人\N{\fs60}I'm not gonna tell you a pack of lies to make me look good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.55,0:04:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我只是告诉你到底发生什么事\N{\fs60}I'm just gonna tell you what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.96,0:04:44.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的名字是尤里·奥洛夫\N{\fs60}My name is Yuri Orlov.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.99,0:04:47.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我年幼时，我们全家来到了美国\N{\fs60}When I was a boy, my family came to America.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.34,0:04:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但没有完全融入美国社会\N{\fs60}But not all the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.20,0:04:53.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}像其他乌克兰人一样 我们都聚集在布莱顿滩\N{\fs60}Like most Ukrainians, we gathered in Brighton Beach.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.74,0:04:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这里可以让我们想起黑海\N{\fs60}It reminded us of the Black Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.23,0:04:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我很快地就意识到我们只是从一个地狱到了另外一个地狱\N{\fs60}I soon realized we'd just swapped one hell for another.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.76,0:05:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}即使在地狱里 天使有时也会出现\N{\fs60}Even in hell, an angel sometimes makes an appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.88,0:05:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我十岁时就崇拜艾娃·方田\N{\fs60}I'd worshipped Ava Fontaine since I was 10 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.71,0:05:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她当然不知道我的存在\N{\fs60}Of course, she didn't know I existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.48,0:05:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有的时候我自己也这么觉得\N{\fs60}I was starting to think she had a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.29,0:05:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在我生命的前二十几年里\N{\fs60}For the first twenty-odd years of my life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.60,0:05:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}小奥德萨对我来说 就像对这列火车一样\N{\fs60}...Little Odessa was to me what it is to the Q train...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.26,0:05:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是终点站\N{\fs60}...the end of the line.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.26,0:05:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(1436,900.7)}小奥德萨           纽约         1982
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.97,0:05:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}哦，关于我的名字，我刚撒了个谎\N{\fs60}Oh, I did lie about my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.49,0:05:32.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}其实并不是尤里·奥洛夫\N{\fs60}It's not really Yuri Orlov.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.63,0:05:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在20世纪的某些时候做个犹太人是有好处的\N{\fs60}There've been few occasions in the in the 20th century when it's been an advantage be a Jew.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.30,0:05:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}70年代我们全家为了逃离苏联\N{\fs60}But in the 'seventies, to escape the Soviet Union,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.89,0:05:41.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就伪装成犹太人\N{\fs60}our family pretended to be Jewish.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.13,0:05:44.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}从此我就活得不怎么好\N{\fs60}Little about my life has been kosher ever since
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.11,0:05:46.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}老哥，你好吗？\N{\fs60}How's it going, brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.71,0:05:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不怎么样\N{\fs60}It's not.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.15,0:05:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是维塔利，我弟弟\N{\fs60}That's Vitaly, my younger brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:05:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他和我一样，对生命感到迷惘\N{\fs60}He was as lost as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.43,0:05:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}只是他现在还不知道罢了\N{\fs60}He didn't know it yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.75,0:05:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里 你迟到了\N{\fs60}Yuri, you're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.11,0:06:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我父亲很快地就把 这伪装的身份当真了\N{\fs60}My father took his assumed identity to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.22,0:06:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他比很多犹太人更犹太\N{\fs60}He was more Jewish than most Jews.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.66,0:06:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这使我信天主教的母亲很生气\N{\fs60}Which drove my Catholic mother crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.95,0:06:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}说过多少次啦？\N{\fs60}How many times?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.06,0:06:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不能吃贝类\N{\fs60}I can't eat shellfish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.56,0:06:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不圣洁\N{\fs60}It's treyf.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.39,0:06:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不是犹太人\N{\fs60}You're not Jewish.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.59,0:06:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但我喜欢这样\N{\fs60}I like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.99,0:06:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我喜欢帽子\N{\fs60}I like the hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.01,0:06:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}时时提醒我们 上面有人类的主宰\N{\fs60}To remind us there is something above us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.36,0:06:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我喜欢那样想\N{\fs60}I like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.59,0:06:27.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我要去(犹太)教堂\N{\fs60}I'm going to temple.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.79,0:06:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}别去！你比牧师去得还勤\N{\fs60}You're not going to temple. You go to temple more than the rabbi.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.03,0:06:32.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(952,895.3)}你这女人少管我的事
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.83,0:06:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(952,895.3)}老天！你什么时候才能清醒点儿？
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.91,0:06:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里，别忘了去看一看皇宫酒店的特价\N{\fs60}Yuri, don't forget to check the specials at the Palace.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.72,0:06:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在小奥德萨长大\N{\fs60}Growing up in Little Odessa,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.46,0:06:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}人杀人是家常便饭\N{\fs60}murder was everyday part of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.80,0:06:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}俄罗斯黑帮也从苏联移民到了这里\N{\fs60}Russian mobsters had also migrated from the Soviet Union
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.14,0:06:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}而且他们来美国时\N{\fs60}and when they came to America,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.95,0:06:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还带着家伙呢\N{\fs60}their baggage came with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.75,0:06:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}社区里 每天都有些帮派份子斗殴\N{\fs60}There was always some gangster getting whacked in my neighborhood,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.60,0:06:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}只是我从没亲眼见过\N{\fs60}but I'd never seen it with my own eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.02,0:07:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}每次我总是早五分钟\N{\fs60}I had this knack of showing up five minutes before something went down,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.46,0:07:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}或晚五分钟\N{\fs60}or five minutes after.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.08,0:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但那天不一样\N{\fs60}Not that day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.83,0:07:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这一枪打醒了我\N{\fs60}It hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.10,0:07:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就像是枪打在我身上一样震撼\N{\fs60}It couldn't have hit me harder if I was the one who'd been shot.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.64,0:07:36.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你开饭馆\N{\fs60}You go into the restaurant business...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.48,0:07:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是因为人总是要吃饭\N{\fs60}because people are always going to have to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.80,0:07:44.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那天我意识到我的命运是为了提供人们的另一种生活必需品\N{\fs60}That was the day I realized my destiny lay in fulfilling another basic human need.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.12,0:07:50.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}下个安息日，我和父亲一起去教堂\N{\fs60}The next Sabbath, I went to temple with my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.25,0:07:54.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}然而我并不是想要接近上帝\N{\fs60}However, it wasn't God I was trying to get close to.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.61,0:07:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的长子，尤里\N{\fs60}Eli, my eldest son, Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.91,0:08:02.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在那儿我认识了第一把 以色列制的乌兹冲锋枪\N{\fs60}My contact at synagogue landed me my first Israeli-made Uzi submachine guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.38,0:08:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}第一次卖枪的感觉很大程度上就象第一次做爱一样\N{\fs60}The first time you sell a gun is a lot like the first time you have sex.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.16,0:08:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你根本不知道自己在干嘛\N{\fs60}You have absolutely no idea what you're doing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.74,0:08:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}虽然很刺激 但很快就结束了\N{\fs60}But it is exciting and one way or another,it's over way too fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.82,0:08:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}先生们\N{\fs60}Gentlemen.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.63,0:08:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}新型乌兹自动手枪\N{\fs60}The new Uzi machine pistol.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.94,0:08:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}体积虽小，但火力强大\N{\fs60}Big firepower in a small package.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.66,0:08:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这宝贝用的是九毫米凹头子弹\N{\fs60}This little baby uses 9 mm hollow points.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.90,0:08:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}20或25发可扩充式弹夹\N{\fs60}Twenty twenty-five round extendable mags...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.16,0:08:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}枪柄大小可调\N{\fs60}...rear-flip adjustable sights.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.68,0:08:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}消音器是标准装备 后座力极低\N{\fs60}Silencer comes standard. Excellent recoil reduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.82,0:08:35.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}枪口上抬减少四成\N{\fs60}Muzzle jump reduced forty percent.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.37,0:08:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}噪音减少六成\N{\fs60}Sixty percent improved noise suppression.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.24,0:08:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就算你“现在”朝我打完一整夹子弹\N{\fs60}You could pump a mag into me right now
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.43,0:08:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}也不会吵醒隔壁的人\N{\fs60}and never wake the guy in the next room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.31,0:08:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当然这样你就没机会和我再做更大的生意了\N{\fs60}Of course, that would eliminate your opportunity for repeat business.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.87,0:08:52.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我天生就有走私违禁品的才能\N{\fs60}I did have a natural instinct for smuggling contraband.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.38,0:08:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}幸运的是那时的摄像机有火箭筒那么大\N{\fs60}Fortunately, back then a video camera was a big as a bazooka
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.26,0:09:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的一生都在远离暴力\N{\fs60}Here I'd been running away from violence my whole life,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.06,0:09:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但其实我更该接近它才对\N{\fs60} and I should've run towards it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.98,0:09:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是人类的天性\N{\fs60}It's in our nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.57,0:09:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}最初人类遗骸的肋骨腔中就有一个矛箭头\N{\fs60}The earliest human skeletons had spearheads in their rib cages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.33,0:09:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}怎么搞这么久？\N{\fs60}Where have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.84,0:09:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果客人来了怎么办？\N{\fs60}What if we had a customer?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.57,0:09:32.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}上帝保佑美国\N{\fs60}God bless America.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.15,0:09:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}“当心恶犬” 你哪儿来的狗！\N{\fs60}Beware of the dog? You don't have a dog.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.88,0:09:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}想吓人呀？\N{\fs60}Are you trying to scare people?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.92,0:10:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是吓我自己\N{\fs60}No, it's to scare me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.78,0:10:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}随时提醒我内心中的恶犬\N{\fs60}Remind me to be aware of the dog in me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.61,0:10:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它想袭击其他动物\N{\fs60}The dog wants to fuck everything that moves
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.96,0:10:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}和击杀弱小同类的狗\N{\fs60}Wants to fight and kill weaker dogs.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.18,0:10:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}提醒自己要像个人\N{\fs60}I guess it's to remind me to be more human.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.04,0:10:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}做条狗和做个人不是一个概念么？\N{\fs60}Isn't being a dog part of being human?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.83,0:10:17.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}也许你生来就是一条狗呢？\N{\fs60}What if that's the best part of you? The dog part.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.84,0:10:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}其实我们就是两条腿的狗\N{\fs60}What if you're really just a two-legged dog?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.59,0:10:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你得去看心理医生了\N{\fs60}You need to see somebody.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.55,0:10:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这里臭死了\N{\fs60}Stinks in here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.90,0:10:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我总想在有生之年做件大事\N{\fs60}I'd always wanted to do something big with my life
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.62,0:10:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}只是不知道要做什么\N{\fs60}I just didn't know what.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.66,0:10:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但我意识到\N{\fs60}Anyhow, I figured,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.10,0:10:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果我真要去卖枪\N{\fs60}if I was going into the gun trade,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.87,0:10:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就得干大买卖\N{\fs60}I was going aim high.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.74,0:10:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维塔利，别鬼混了，我要和你谈谈\N{\fs60}Vitaly, stop fucking around. I want to talk to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你每天看报纸吗？\N{\fs60}You read the newspapers, Vit?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.32,0:10:48.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}报纸？每天都一样\N{\fs60}Newspaper? It's always the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.76,0:10:49.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没错\N{\fs60}You're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.00,0:10:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}每天都有人在枪战\N{\fs60}Every day there's people shooting each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.22,0:10:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当我看到这种报道时 你猜我会干嘛？\N{\fs60}You know what I do when I see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.48,0:10:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}看他们用什么枪 心想为什么不是我卖的枪\N{\fs60}I look to see what guns they're using and I think to myself, why not my guns?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.99,0:10:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你要开个枪店？\N{\fs60}What, are you opening a gun shop?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.58,0:11:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}美国的枪店已经比麦当劳还多了\N{\fs60}Already more of those in than McDonald's.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.24,0:11:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}即使这附近的黑帮这么多利润还是不够\N{\fs60}Even with all the gangsters around here, the margins are too low.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.12,0:11:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}-你已经算出能赚多少？ -当然！\N{\fs60}You've figured the margins? Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.71,0:11:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}帮派的火拼算个啥！\N{\fs60}Forget gang wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.46,0:11:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真正的战争有血有肉的\N{\fs60}The real money is in actual wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.76,0:11:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}国与国之间的\N{\fs60}Between countries.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.42,0:11:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里 你他娘的懂个屁枪\N{\fs60}Yuri, what the fuck do you know about guns?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.78,0:11:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我知道咱们得干\N{\fs60}I know which end I'd rather be on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.23,0:11:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我做成了第一笔生意\N{\fs60}I made the first sale.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.52,0:11:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这买卖咱们已经在干了\N{\fs60}We're already in business.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.33,0:11:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}呃...咱们？\N{\fs60}Whoa, whoa. We?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.21,0:11:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我要个合伙人\N{\fs60}I need a partner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.19,0:11:37.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不知道...\N{\fs60}I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.13,0:11:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不知道，尤里，我不知道...\N{\fs60}I don't know, Yuri. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.96,0:11:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维塔利，我喝过你煮的罗宋汤\N{\fs60}Vitaly, I've tasted your borscht.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.89,0:11:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不是那块料\N{\fs60}You're no fucking chef.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.01,0:11:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我可以在餐馆吃白食 但我还是不在那儿吃\N{\fs60}I can eat in the restaurant for free and I still don't eat there.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.14,0:11:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}去你妈的\N{\fs60}Fuck you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.57,0:11:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}咱们一生无所事事\N{\fs60}We're doing nothing with our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.66,0:11:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的意思是，现在的生活是一团糟！\N{\fs60}I mean, this is shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.18,0:11:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}的确\N{\fs60}It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.12,0:12:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但或许什么也不做，也比做这个好\N{\fs60}But maybe doing nothing's better than doing this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.42,0:12:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我需要你\N{\fs60}I need you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.04,0:12:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}哥们儿就是哥们儿
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.38,0:12:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}哥们儿就是哥们儿
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.42,0:12:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}先生...\N{\fs60}Sir,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.68,0:12:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有没兴趣看看S7地对空飞弹\N{\fs60}may I interest you in the shoulder-fired SA-7 surface-to-air missiles?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.06,0:12:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}中国制，过时的型号\N{\fs60}The older Chinese model.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.42,0:12:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}用在现代军事战机上或许不行\N{\fs60}Not so effective against modern military aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.86,0:12:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不过打打商业客机还是挺不错的\N{\fs60}But deadly if used against a commercial airliner.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.64,0:12:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}$850而已，等于是送给你了\N{\fs60}I'm giving them away at 8-50.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.14,0:12:50.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那是80年代，冷战尚未结束\N{\fs60}In the '80s, and the Cold War was far from thawed
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}多数的交易是政府之间的\N{\fs60}Most of the deals were government-to-government.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.00,0:12:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}几乎都是私人军火俱乐部 而且主席都是终生职\N{\fs60}It was a mostly private club with a lifetime club president.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.33,0:12:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就是他\N{\fs60}That's him.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.58,0:12:59.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那个大人物？\N{\fs60}The big shot?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.28,0:13:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}席米恩·怀斯\N{\fs60}Simeon Weisz,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.88,0:13:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}安哥拉、莫桑比克等国的代表\N{\fs60} Angola, Mozambique, those Exocet missiles in the Falklands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.65,0:13:08.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}火药还没发明前，他就已经在卖枪\N{\fs60}He was selling guns before there was gunpowder.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.56,0:13:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}马上回来\N{\fs60}Be right back.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.85,0:13:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}怀斯先生...怀斯先生！\N{\fs60}Mr. Weisz? Mr. Weisz!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.19,0:13:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没关系，他们只是谈一谈\N{\fs60}It's okay, they're talking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.57,0:13:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我可以帮助你吗？\N{\fs60}May I help?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.71,0:13:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}布莱顿滩进出口公司的伊莱·克兹曼\N{\fs60}A mutual friend, Eli Kurtzman from Brighton Beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.62,0:13:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}您我都认识的 要我来与您联系\N{\fs60}import/export said to contact you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.98,0:13:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我有一个生意企划\N{\fs60}I have a business proposal
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.66,0:13:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}或许我们能讨论一下\N{\fs60}and I thought perhaps we could discuss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.11,0:13:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想我们不是做同一种生意\N{\fs60}I don't think you and I are in the same business.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.82,0:13:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你以为我只是卖枪的军火商，对吧？\N{\fs60}You think I just sell guns, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.09,0:13:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不对！我是有立场的\N{\fs60}I don't. I take sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.96,0:13:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但两伊战争中，您卖过军火给双方\N{\fs60}But in the Iran-lraq war you sold guns to both sides.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.11,0:13:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你有没想过，或许我想让两边都输\N{\fs60}Did you ever consider that I wanted both sides to lose?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.86,0:13:50.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}用枪杆来换个政府，比用选票更有效\N{\fs60}Bullets change governments far surer than votes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}朋友，你来错地方了\N{\fs60}You're in the wrong place, my young friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.51,0:13:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这里不是玩票的人该来的\N{\fs60}This is no place for amateurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.15,0:14:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}操他妈
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.18,0:14:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}奇怪的是，当你很生气时 你很自然地会说起家乡话来\N{\fs60}Curious how you always revert to your native tongue in moments of extreme anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.26,0:14:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}和很爽的时候\N{\fs60}And ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.74,0:14:15.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}主啊...主啊，哦，主啊！
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.08,0:14:22.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你真漂亮\N{\fs60}You are beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.30,0:14:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你叫什么名字来着？\N{\fs60}What's your name again?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.83,0:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我和维塔利只能做地下买卖\N{\fs60}The only option for Vitaly and me was under-the-counter gunrunning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.73,0:14:39.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(404,900.7)}黎巴嫩，1984
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.81,0:14:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}黎巴嫩开始有自杀式爆炸后我的生意终于有了突破\N{\fs60}I got my first break in Lebanon after the suicide bombing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.82,0:14:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但我并不是唯一在当地赚到钱的人\N{\fs60}But I wasn't the only local kid making good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.82,0:14:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当美国撤离一个战区时\N{\fs60}When the United States leaves a war zone...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.89,0:14:53.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们通常不把武器带走\N{\fs60}they generally don't take their munitions.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.71,0:14:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}因为运回去 比买新的还贵\N{\fs60}It costs more to bring it back than to buy new stock.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.27,0:15:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们是按公斤卖的\N{\fs60}So, we sell by the kilo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.82,0:15:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}虽然是二手货 但还是很好用\N{\fs60}They're secondhand weapons,but they're still okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.97,0:15:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你要买多少公斤？\N{\fs60}How many kilos would you like?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.71,0:15:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}五千公斤\N{\fs60}Five thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.80,0:15:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我虽有点儿语言天才\N{\fs60}I had a flair for languages...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但我很快发现，谈美元、卢比、卢布、英镑\N{\fs60}...but I soon discovered that what talks best is dollars, dinars drachmas, rubles, rupees,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.93,0:15:19.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这些才是最好的\N{\fs60}and pounds-fucking-sterling.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.90,0:15:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当然，美国陆军也插了一脚\N{\fs60}Of course, the U.S. Army got a piece of the action.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.08,0:15:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}80年代陆军薪资很低，即使现在也一样\N{\fs60}Army salaries were no better then than they are today.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.59,0:15:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}而其中有些军官 像陆军的撒登中校\N{\fs60}And some of the brass, like Lieutenant Colonel Southern...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.71,0:15:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}需要钱来进行他私人的战争\N{\fs60}needed to raise money for their own private wars.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.51,0:15:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}很高兴认识你\N{\fs60}Good to make your acquaintance.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.92,0:15:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这点钱算个屁\N{\fs60}This is bullshit money,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.04,0:15:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还不够塞牙缝\N{\fs60}This is small-fucking-potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.24,0:15:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}啥？你想做“正当”的生意？\N{\fs60}What do you want to do, go more legit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.92,0:15:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不，是更加“不合法”\N{\fs60}No, more illegal.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.34,0:15:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我现在只想要一盘卷心菜和马铃薯\N{\fs60}What I would give right now for cabbage and potatoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.74,0:16:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这不关我们的事\N{\fs60}It's not our fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.16,0:16:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维，快吧！\N{\fs60}Vit, come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.75,0:16:20.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}咱们走，快\N{\fs60}Let's go. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.27,0:16:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}卖枪就像卖吸尘器一样\N{\fs60}Selling guns is like selling vacuum cleaners.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.81,0:16:35.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}打电话\N{\fs60}You make calls,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.93,0:16:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谈价钱\N{\fs60}pound the pavement,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.88,0:16:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}处理订单\N{\fs60}take orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.90,0:16:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我是什么都做的死亡商人\N{\fs60}I was an equal opportunity merchant of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.30,0:16:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}除了救世军之外 不管什么军我都卖\N{\fs60}I supplied every army but the Salvation Army.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.30,0:16:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\fs80\an7}救世军：国际性宗教及慈善公益组织
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.88,0:16:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我把乌兹枪卖给穆斯林\N{\fs60}I sold Israeli-made Uzis to Muslims.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.14,0:16:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我把共产主义造的子弹 卖给法西斯主义\N{\fs60}I sold communist-made bullets to fascists.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.91,0:16:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(942,844)}奥洛夫先生，希望你 不是打算要卖这个东西
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.91,0:17:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}是...个人用的
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.45,0:17:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}这里有10万发子弹
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.62,0:17:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}我比较喜欢打枪
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.33,0:17:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}喜欢打枪？
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.49,0:17:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我还把军火运到阿富汗 尽管他们在打我的苏联盟军\N{\fs60}I even shipped cargo to Afghanistan when they were still fighting my fellow Soviets.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.32,0:17:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我从来没卖给本·拉登\N{\fs60}I never sold to Osama Bin Laden.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.67,0:17:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不是因为道德问题\N{\fs60}Not on any moral grounds.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.26,0:17:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}而是那时他的支票总是跳票\N{\fs60}Back then, he was always bouncing checks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.38,0:17:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}80年代中期\N{\fs60}By the mid-'80s...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.64,0:17:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的武器被用在世界前10名的战区中的8个\N{\fs60}my weapons were represented in eight of the world's top ten war zones.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.03,0:18:10.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有双重身份的生活不是什么问题\N{\fs60}There's no problem leading a double life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.07,0:18:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但三重、四重身份最终才会出问题\N{\fs60}It's the triple and quadruple lives that get you in the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.20,0:18:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那时我带着法国、英国、以色列、和乌克兰的护照\N{\fs60}Back then, I carried a... French, British, Israeli,and Ukrainian passport...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.51,0:18:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还有美国的学生签证\N{\fs60}...and a student visa for the U.S.,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.36,0:18:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但那是另一个故事啦\N{\fs60}but... that's another story.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.03,0:18:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我还有6个手提箱\N{\fs60}I also packed six different briefcases...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.48,0:18:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}用于不同的地区和不同的身份\N{\fs60}...depending on who I was that day and the region of the world I was visiting.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.54,0:18:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(1376,892.6)}卡塔赫纳港口北部  哥伦比亚 - 1989
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.79,0:18:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果没有我\N{\fs60}Without operations like mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.34,0:18:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有些国家根本打不了一场像样的战争\N{\fs60}would be impossible for certain countries to conduct a respectable war.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.32,0:18:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}虽然武器禁运有点儿不方便 不过还难不倒我\N{\fs60}I was able to navigate around those inconvenient little arms embargoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.59,0:18:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}世上一共有三种基本的军火交易\N{\fs60}There are three basic types of arms deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.86,0:18:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}白色，合法的\N{\fs60}White, being legal.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.23,0:18:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}黑色，违法的\N{\fs60}Black, being illegal,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还有我最中意的颜色...灰色\N{\fs60}and my personal favorite color, gray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.64,0:18:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有时我把交易弄得太复杂\N{\fs60}Sometimes I made the deal so convoluted...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.20,0:18:57.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就连我自己也搞不清楚\N{\fs60}it was hard for me to work out if they were on the level.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.16,0:19:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为了避开执法人员 我通常使用暗语\N{\fs60}To keep authorities in the dark, I often spoke in code.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.45,0:19:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}妈妈是火箭发射器\N{\fs60}Rocket launchers were "mothers."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.06,0:19:04.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}孩子是火箭\N{\fs60}The rockets, "children."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.42,0:19:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}AK-47自动步枪是天使王\N{\fs60}The AK-47 assault rifle was the "Angel King."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.46,0:19:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我是尤里 嗯...是...拉伍...\N{\fs60}It's Yuri... Yeah. Well, Raoul...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.55,0:19:16.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}拉伍，天使王明天会到\N{\fs60}Raoul, the Angel King will arrive tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.16,0:19:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你也是，哈利路亚，呵呵\N{\fs60}Hallelujah to you, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.27,0:19:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果我不出纰漏的话\N{\fs60}The point is, if I've done my job right
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.86,0:19:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}武器禁运法根本无法执行\N{\fs60}an arms embargo should be practically impossible to enforce.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.47,0:19:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}什么？\N{\fs60}What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.28,0:19:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}妈的，慢慢讲！\N{\fs60}Okay, just slow the fuck down.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.36,0:19:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不知道你在说什么\N{\fs60}I can't understand you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.89,0:19:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}“走漏消息”是什么意思？\N{\fs60}Wha-What do you mean, tipped off?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.78,0:19:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们知道我们在哪儿？ 他们在哪儿？\N{\fs60}They know where we are? Well, where are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.76,0:19:42.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我还有多少时间？ 不多了？\N{\fs60}Well, how long have I got? Not long?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.53,0:19:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}啥意思？妈的！\N{\fs60}What does that mean? Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.55,0:19:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}要我甩掉他们吗？ 用这种船？\N{\fs60}Do we try to lose them? On this?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.40,0:19:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里，我们得避一避\N{\fs60}Yuri, we have to get off this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.94,0:19:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不，谁也不准离开\N{\fs60}No. No one's going anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.50,0:19:51.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}减速，减到非常慢 给我争取点时间\N{\fs60}Slow, dead slow. Buy me time.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.06,0:19:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是，我是尤里\N{\fs60}Yeah, it's Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.40,0:19:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}把那个蠢旗摘下来！\N{\fs60}Get that fucking rag down!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.66,0:20:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我需要另一个船名\N{\fs60}I need another handle for this tub.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.50,0:20:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}和我们大小和吨位相当的\N{\fs60}Something in our weight class.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.60,0:20:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你，快下去 我们要换名字了\N{\fs60}You! Over the side. We're changing the name. Now!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.75,0:20:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在！当然要真的名字！\N{\fs60}Yes, it's got to check out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.93,0:20:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就我来说\N{\fs60}The way I look at it,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.16,0:20:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}名字不重要\N{\fs60}what's in a name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.83,0:20:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有短一点的名字吗？\N{\fs60}Have you got a shorter name?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.13,0:20:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我常更换船和飞机注册的名字\N{\fs60}I'd often changed the registration of a ship or a plane...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.40,0:20:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但从来没有这么急过\N{\fs60}...but never on such short notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.96,0:20:24.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}妈的，来得真快！\N{\fs60}Damn! They're hauling.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.83,0:20:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}什么？KONO？怎么拼？\N{\fs60}What? Kono? How do you spell that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.73,0:20:30.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}K-O-N-O，很好\N{\fs60}K-O-N-O, okay, well, that's good.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.68,0:20:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}KONO，K-O-N-O\N{\fs60}Kono, K-O-N-O.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.79,0:20:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}挂什么国旗？荷兰，好\N{\fs60}What are we flying? Dutch? Got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.92,0:20:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}拿个荷兰国旗给我\N{\fs60}Vit, get me a Dutch flag, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.59,0:20:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}快，否则我把你扔到海里\N{\fs60}Faster! Or I'll send your ass in!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.71,0:20:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里，找不到荷兰  - 什么！？\N{\fs60}Yuri, I don't have Dutch!   - What?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.79,0:20:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有比利时的\N{\fs60}I've got Belgian.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.90,0:20:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有屁用 刚漆上的船名是在荷兰注册的\N{\fs60}What the fuck use is that? He's painting a name registered in the fucking Netherlands.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.93,0:21:02.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我有个法国国旗  - 所以呢？\N{\fs60}I've got a French flag.   - So?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.41,0:21:03.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}横过来...\N{\fs60}Turn it sideways...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.46,0:21:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就是荷兰\N{\fs60}...it's Dutch.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.10,0:21:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这就是为什么你是我弟弟\N{\fs60}That's why you're my brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.28,0:21:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好极了\N{\fs60}All right, good!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.40,0:21:34.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}每个人都要装无辜样\N{\fs60}Everybody look innocent now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.63,0:21:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}俗话说，人人都有个价码\N{\fs60}They say every man has his price.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.33,0:21:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但不是每个人都能得到\N{\fs60}But not every man gets it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.10,0:21:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}国际警察杰克·瓦伦丁就无法被收买\N{\fs60}Interpol Agent Jack Valentine couldn't be bought.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.11,0:21:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}至少用钱买不到\N{\fs60}At least, not with money.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.20,0:21:55.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}对杰克来说，荣誉才是他的价码\N{\fs60}For Jack, glory was the prize.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.20,0:21:58.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}嗯...是柯诺号，不是克里斯多号\N{\fs60}Yeah, it's the Kono; it's not the Kristol.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.06,0:22:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}柯诺，K-O-N-O\N{\fs60}Kono, K-O-N-O.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.46,0:22:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这船没问题，长官\N{\fs60}It's clean, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.96,0:22:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没问题？\N{\fs60}It's clean?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.33,0:22:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}可看起来不像\N{\fs60}It sure doesn't look clean.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.33,0:22:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我要登船检查\N{\fs60}I'm going to go aboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.93,0:22:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}发讯号让他们以为 克里斯多号在阿鲁巴岛南方\N{\fs60}Phone in a sighting of the Kristol south of Aruba.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.20,0:22:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}即使当我遭遇称职的国际警察时\N{\fs60}Even when I was up against an overzealous agent...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.90,0:22:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我还是有很多方法来防止他们搜查\N{\fs60}...I had a number of methods for discouraging a search.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.36,0:22:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我经常把装军火的箱子标示成“农用机械”\N{\fs60}I routinely mislabeled my arms shipments "Farm Machinery."
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.06,0:22:31.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我还将集装箱标识为有化学辐射\N{\fs60}And I have yet to meet the lowly paid customs official...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.05,0:22:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我还没见过哪个低薪的海关人员\N{\fs60}who will open a container marked
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.66,0:22:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}会愿意打开“辐射废料”的箱子来核对\N{\fs60} "Radioactive Waste" to verify its contents.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.36,0:22:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不过我最喜欢的技俩是一箱\N{\fs60}But my personal favorite is the unique combination...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.99,0:22:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在热带烈阳下晒了一星期的马铃薯\N{\fs60}of week-old potatoes and tropical heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.90,0:22:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真难闻\N{\fs60}Smells.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.40,0:23:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}长官，克里斯多号在我们北方出现\N{\fs60}Sir, Sighting of the Kristol, due north.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.17,0:23:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}最重要的是我会收买一些情报人员\N{\fs60}Most importantly, I kept a number of intelligence people on the payroll to supply their colleagues
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.93,0:23:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}以便适时地向同僚提供假情报\N{\fs60}with counterintelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.06,0:23:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们走\N{\fs60}Let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.23,0:23:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}走私枪支的第二条守则是\N{\fs60}The second rule of gunrunning is:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.28,0:23:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}每次都要确定能收到钱\N{\fs60}Always ensure you have a foolproof way to get paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.39,0:23:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}最好是\N{\fs60}Preferably in advance...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.04,0:23:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}事先付款至海外的帐户\N{\fs60}ideally to an off-shore account.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.23,0:23:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这就是为什么 我如此小心筛选客户的原因\N{\fs60}That's why I chose my customers so carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.96,0:23:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我喜欢军阀和独裁者\N{\fs60}Say what you like about warlords and dictators...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.67,0:23:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们通常很讲义气\N{\fs60}they tend to have a highly developed sense of order.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.36,0:23:43.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}总是准时付钱\N{\fs60}They always pay their bills on time.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.86,0:23:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}这是什么？
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.86,0:23:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(956,895.3)}6公斤的纯海洛因
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.19,0:23:52.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(950,841.3)}我总不能把这个存进曼哈顿的银行吧
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.28,0:23:56.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,833.2)}听请楚咯，你这混蛋 你该感谢我才对
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:23:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(962,841.3)}你查了今天市场的价格吗？
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.04,0:24:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(956,838.6)}上周在边界有一堆货被查扣 现在价格涨了三成
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.05,0:24:09.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(970,892.6)}我是卖枪的，不是贩毒的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.51,0:24:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,895.3)}多样化能降低风险
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.72,0:24:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,895.3)}我是有原则的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.30,0:24:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}你不给钱，我就不玩了
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.51,0:24:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(946,895.3)}去你妈的
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.38,0:24:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你想干嘛？\N{\fs60}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.50,0:24:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}操你！\N{\fs60}Fuck you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.53,0:24:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}操你！\N{\fs60}Fuck you!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.39,0:24:23.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(936,835.9)}别操了 总有解决办法
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.04,0:24:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不要，维！\N{\fs60}No, Vit!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.48,0:24:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(980,892.6)}成交！成交！
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.62,0:24:34.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}走私枪支第一条也是最重要的守则是\N{\fs60}The first and most important rule of gunrunning...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.89,0:24:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}别被自己买卖的商品打伤了\N{\fs60}is never get shot with your own merchandise.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.43,0:24:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你没事儿吧？\N{\fs60}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.79,0:24:41.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想是\N{\fs60}I think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.06,0:24:44.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们现在该怎么办？\N{\fs60}So what do we do now?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.32,0:24:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们庆祝一下\N{\fs60}Let's celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.50,0:25:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那个北哥伦比亚的游击份子说得没错\N{\fs60}That narco guerilla had his facts right.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:12.88,0:25:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}美国边境的缉毒行动\N{\fs60}After shipping it stateside, the return on that blow
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.15,0:25:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}的确为我带来可观的利润\N{\fs60}netted me a healthy profit.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.31,0:25:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}要不是半途丢了一公斤\N{\fs60}It would have been even better,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.75,0:25:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}利润会更可观\N{\fs60}except one kilo never made it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.36,0:25:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维塔利?\N{\fs60}Vitaly?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.72,0:25:24.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维!\N{\fs60}Vit!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.58,0:25:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}直至今日我还不知道维在逃避什么\N{\fs60}To this day I don't know what Vitaly was running away from.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.14,0:25:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}或许是在逃避他自己吧\N{\fs60}Maybe just from Vitaly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.18,0:25:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}12天后 我在两千哩外\N{\fs60}I found him twelve days, two thousand miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.72,0:25:39.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}玻利维亚边境的寄宿屋子里找到了他\N{\fs60}and one hundred and fifty grams later
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.42,0:25:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还吸了150公克\N{\fs60}in a Bolivian boarding house.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.08,0:25:48.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没想到，我的梦中情人 早我一步来到了这里\N{\fs60}Of course, my dream girl had gone there before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.40,0:25:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维!\N{\fs60}Vit!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:06.33,0:26:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}快开门!\N{\fs60}Come on!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.30,0:26:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}妈的!尤里回来了\N{\fs60}Fuck, Yuri's back.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.70,0:26:27.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我哥哥，尤里\N{\fs60}It's my brother, Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.32,0:26:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的大哥哥\N{\fs60}He's my big brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.20,0:26:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}妈的，那是什么？\N{\fs60}What the fuck is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.64,0:26:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}乌克兰\N{\fs60}Ukraine.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.08,0:26:37.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}虽然当时我还年幼，但我记得\N{\fs60}I was young, but I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.39,0:26:40.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}瞧，我从奥德萨...\N{\fs60}Look... I start in Odessa, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.75,0:26:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}到克米恩\N{\fs60}And then I work my way to the Crimean
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.68,0:26:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}到了基辅你就没命了!\N{\fs60}You'll be dead before you fucking reach Kiev!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.07,0:26:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}快，咱们回家吧\N{\fs60}We're going home. Come on,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.18,0:26:50.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你...我操...\N{\fs60}You fuck! You fucking fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.76,0:26:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}操...操\N{\fs60}You fucking fuck...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.75,0:26:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你有啥问题啊！\N{\fs60}What the fuck is your problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.29,0:27:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}走吧，维\N{\fs60}Come on, Vit.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.43,0:27:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(482,892.6)}肯尼迪国际机场 - 纽约 - 1989
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.93,0:27:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}回家真好\N{\fs60}Yuri, it's so nice to be home.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.00,0:27:09.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}嗯...我会带你回家\N{\fs60}We're gonna get you home.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.55,0:27:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}来\N{\fs60}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.48,0:27:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(952,830.5)}圣法兰西斯戒毒所
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.55,0:27:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}下车吧\N{\fs60}Get out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.16,0:27:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维塔利，我要你下车\N{\fs60}Vitaly, I need you to get out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.82,0:27:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我对父母发过誓\N{\fs60}I promised our parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.31,0:27:36.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}别\N{\fs60}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.42,0:27:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维塔利，你会很满意的\N{\fs60}Vitaly, you're going to have a great time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.11,0:27:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是好地方\N{\fs60}This is a top place.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.13,0:27:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}上周有两个杂志模特\N{\fs60}Two Ford models checked in last week.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.89,0:27:43.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还有报气象的美女六月就来了\N{\fs60}And that cute weather girl's been here since July.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.04,0:27:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}别\N{\fs60}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.27,0:27:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}求你了，尤里\N{\fs60}Please, Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.66,0:28:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你是好哥哥\N{\fs60}You're a good brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.31,0:28:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你是好哥哥，尤里\N{\fs60}You're a good brother, Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.88,0:28:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}嗯...好了\N{\fs60}Okay. All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.08,0:28:13.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好哥哥\N{\fs60}Good brother.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.02,0:28:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}下车吧...\N{\fs60}All right. Get out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.67,0:28:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好吧\N{\fs60}Okay
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.10,0:28:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}下车吧\N{\fs60}Get out of the car.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.56,0:28:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那时起我就单独行动了\N{\fs60}From then on I was a one-man operation.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.22,0:28:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我从没搞清楚偶而吸毒玩玩和吸上的毒瘾有什么分别\N{\fs60}I never understood what separated the recreational drug user from the habitual.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.81,0:28:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}上帝见证 还好我自己没有吸上瘾\N{\fs60}But for the grace of God it could've been me snorting lines as long as the Belt Parkway.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.19,0:28:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是我还是没能逃脱\N{\fs60}However, I wasn't entirely free
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.26,0:28:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}某种令人上瘾的东西\N{\fs60}of the grip of addiction myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.26,0:28:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她又出现了\N{\fs60}There she was again.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.87,0:28:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}艾娃·方田\N{\fs60}Ava Fontaine.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.70,0:28:48.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们那儿的街坊邻居说\N{\fs60}In my neighborhood they say,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.30,0:28:49.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}能走出这里才算有出息\N{\fs60}"The good get out."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.59,0:28:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我和她都用各自的方式，征服了世界\N{\fs60}In our own ways, we'd both conquered the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.58,0:28:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(514,938.5)}圣巴兹岛 - 法属加勒比海 - 1989
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.78,0:29:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不能强迫一个人爱上你\N{\fs60}You can't force somebody to fall in love with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.82,0:29:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但起码你可以制造机会\N{\fs60}But you can definitely improve your odds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.09,0:29:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我花了两万元搞个假拍照活动骗她来\N{\fs60}It cost me 20 grand to book he for a fake photo shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.08,0:29:19.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}又花了一万二买通旅馆\N{\fs60}Another twelve to buy out the hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.84,0:30:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}很受欢迎的旅馆，对吧？\N{\fs60}Popular hotel, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.61,0:30:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}艾娃·方田 - 尤里·奥洛夫\N{\fs60}Ava Fontaine. - Yuri Orlov.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.21,0:30:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为何事来这儿？\N{\fs60}What brings you to St. Barts?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.68,0:30:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}拍照\N{\fs60}Photo shoot.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.58,0:30:15.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}至少原来是这么安排的\N{\fs60}At least, that was the plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.50,0:30:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}摄影师被困在迈阿密了\N{\fs60}I guess the photographer got stuck in Miami.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.05,0:30:21.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}说有飓风，但新闻上只字未提\N{\fs60}Hurricane. Though there's nothing on the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.44,0:30:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这种事儿总是突如其来\N{\fs60}Those things can come out of nowhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.42,0:30:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}拍照取消了\N{\fs60}So... the job's been cancelled,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.55,0:30:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}更麻烦的是星期二才有飞机去纽约\N{\fs60}and wouldn't you know it, there's no flight to New York until Tuesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.41,0:30:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果你愿意，可以搭我的飞机，我明天走\N{\fs60}You can hitch a ride with me if you like. I'm leaving tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.65,0:30:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}趁此，不如我替你照张像吧\N{\fs60}Meanwhile, why don't I take your picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.64,0:30:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}经验告诉我\N{\fs60}In my experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.97,0:30:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}最成功的两人关系 都是从谎言和欺骗开始的\N{\fs60}some of the most successful relationships are based on lies and deceit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.85,0:30:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}关系发展到最后也是撒谎和欺骗\N{\fs60}Since that's where they usually end up anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.90,0:30:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不如就这样开始吧\N{\fs60}it's a logical place to start.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.82,0:30:50.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就那儿，别动\N{\fs60}Right there. Hold it there.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.70,0:30:52.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的天啊！\N{\fs60}Oh, my God!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.10,0:30:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为了让她相信我的财富 使我几乎破产\N{\fs60}I nearly went broke trying to convince her I was anything but.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.11,0:31:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不信她会被能搭一趟私人飞机所诱惑\N{\fs60}I knew Ava was not the kind of woman to be seduced by a ride in a private jet
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.78,0:31:06.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}除非飞机是我的\N{\fs60}unless you owned the jet.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.05,0:31:08.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是你的飞机吗？\N{\fs60}This is your plane?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.50,0:31:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那是我的名字\N{\fs60}That is my name.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.44,0:31:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我当然在撒谎\N{\fs60}Of course, I was lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.87,0:31:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}飞机是租的，还有车子和身上的西装\N{\fs60}The plane was rented, like the car and even the suit I was standing in
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.59,0:31:18.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}起飞前我才贿赂机员 漆上我的名字\N{\fs60}At the last minute,I'd bribed the crew for the paint job.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.75,0:31:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还好降落前\N{\fs60}Luckily, by the time we landed...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.81,0:31:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她的眼睛没离开过我身上\N{\fs60}Ava wasn't looking anywhere but in my eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.63,0:31:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我居然浑然不知\N{\fs60}I had no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.59,0:31:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真抱歉我没认出你\N{\fs60}I'm sorry I didn't recognize you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.66,0:31:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不用道歉啦 我穿各种衣服只是为了挣钱罢了\N{\fs60}Don't apologize. I put clothes on for a living.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.98,0:31:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我倒希望你脱下来\N{\fs60}A least you're not taking them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.63,0:31:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}假如摄影师能来那我就会脱了\N{\fs60}I would be, if half the photographers had their way.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.96,0:31:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你呢？\N{\fs60}What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.52,0:31:40.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我做运输生意\N{\fs60}I'm in transport.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.93,0:31:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}大部份是国际空运\N{\fs60}International air freight, mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.37,0:31:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}生意很好吧\N{\fs60}Business is good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.33,0:31:47.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你是哪儿人？\N{\fs60}Where're you from?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.85,0:31:49.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我生在乌克兰，在纽约布鲁克林长大\N{\fs60}I was born in Ukraine, but I grew up in Brooklyn.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.04,0:31:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不会吧！\N{\fs60}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.06,0:31:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}怎么了？你也是？\N{\fs60}What, you too?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.10,0:31:53.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}(乌克兰)威廉堡\N{\fs60}Williamsburg.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.93,0:31:59.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那...敬飓风一杯\N{\fs60}Here's to a hurricane.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.40,0:32:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果没它，我就不会认识你\N{\fs60}Without it, I never would have met you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.98,0:32:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这可不是巧合，尤里\N{\fs60}This is no accident, is it, Yuri?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.86,0:32:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是命运的安排\N{\fs60}It feels like fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.52,0:32:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不信命运\N{\fs60}I don't believe in fate.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.63,0:32:17.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那你信什么？\N{\fs60}What do you believe in?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.32,0:33:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}风景漂亮，还是你漂亮？\N{\fs60}Is that a view, or is that a view?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.20,0:33:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是风景啦\N{\fs60}That's a view.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.69,0:33:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谢谢...谢谢大家\N{\fs60}Thank you. Thank you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.34,0:33:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}恭喜你\N{\fs60}Congratulations.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.49,0:33:24.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谢谢\N{\fs60}Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.75,0:33:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}别忘了，儿子\N{\fs60}Always remember, son...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.50,0:33:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}总是会有些东西是在你之上的\N{\fs60}There is something above you.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.20,0:33:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}会的，爸爸\N{\fs60}Sure, Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.54,0:33:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}四万元的水晶吊灯嘛\N{\fs60}A forty-thousand-dollar crystal chandelier.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.82,0:33:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}别拘束，随处转转\N{\fs60}Make yourselves at home. Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.96,0:33:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}走啊!\N{\fs60}Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.43,0:33:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}对不起，你一定很难过\N{\fs60}I'm sorry. Today must be tough.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.90,0:34:02.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}今天如果我的爸妈能来 那就好了\N{\fs60}It'd be nice to have a couple more guests from my side of the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.24,0:34:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们现在一定在天上看着你\N{\fs60}I'm sure they're watching right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.17,0:34:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谢谢\N{\fs60}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.53,0:34:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是你不信这些，尤里\N{\fs60}But you don't believe that, Yuri
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.57,0:34:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还记得吗？\N{\fs60}...remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.35,0:34:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我了解你，尤里\N{\fs60}I know you, Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.22,0:34:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我知道你不像表面上那样风光\N{\fs60}I know you're not everything you seem.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.13,0:34:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}别担心，我不会问很多问题的\N{\fs60}Don't worry, I won't ask a lot of questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.65,0:34:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}因为我不想听你撒谎\N{\fs60}I don't want to hear you lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.62,0:34:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你常挺而走险\N{\fs60}You take risks.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.80,0:34:31.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}答应我，别把全家赔上了\N{\fs60}Just promise me you won't risk us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.30,0:34:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这就是爱上梦中情人的麻烦\N{\fs60}That's the trouble with falling in love with a dream girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.16,0:34:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她们会突然成为现实\N{\fs60}They have a habit of becoming real.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.86,0:34:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}见到维塔利，我从没这么高兴过\N{\fs60}I've never been so glad to see Vitaly.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.06,0:34:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你们真他娘的天生一对儿\N{\fs60}You're fucking beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.66,0:34:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}老哥\N{\fs60}Brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.65,0:34:55.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谢谢你给我这么漂亮的嫂子\N{\fs60}Brother, thank you so much for giving me such a beautiful sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.62,0:34:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}出了戒毒所，他乐疯了\N{\fs60}He was out of rehab, and out of his mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:58.29,0:35:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}跳舞，跳舞，跳舞！\N{\fs60}Dance! Dance! We have to dance!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.46,0:35:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}得好好庆祝婚礼！\N{\fs60}All right, all right It's a wedding, a celebration
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.19,0:35:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}敬尤里！\N{\fs60}To Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.00,0:35:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有一次，他救了我一命\N{\fs60}For once, he rescued me.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.66,0:35:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(496,889.9)}纽约 - 12月25日 - 1991
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.96,0:35:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我依旧超支度日\N{\fs60}I was still living way beyond my means.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.09,0:35:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}房贷超高 以信用卡养信用卡\N{\fs60}Mortgaged to the hilt, using one credit card to pay another.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.65,0:35:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我以前宠惯了她现在只好拼命想办法\N{\fs60}Anything to keep Ava in the style to which she had thanks largely to me
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.87,0:35:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}才能维持她以往的生活水平\N{\fs60}become accustomed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.29,0:35:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}艾娃，这太贵重了\N{\fs60}Ava, this is too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.11,0:35:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里很宠爱你的\N{\fs60}Yuri likes to spoil you.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.68,0:35:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}突然间\N{\fs60}Then suddenly,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.56,0:35:27.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我所有的圣诞礼物都一起来了\N{\fs60}all my Christmases came at once.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.41,0:35:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尼奇，你会走啦!好孩子!\N{\fs60}Nicki, you did it! Good boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.14,0:35:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这才像我孙子!\N{\fs60}That's my grandson!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.56,0:35:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里，快来看你儿子在干嘛\N{\fs60}Yuri, don't you want to see what your son is doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.85,0:35:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}说施比受更有福的人\N{\fs60}Whoever said it's better to give than receive...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.14,0:35:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一定没收过\N{\fs60}...never got a Christmas present like the one I got...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.63,0:35:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}像1991年戈巴契夫给我这样的礼物\N{\fs60}in 1991 from Mikhail Gorbachev.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.68,0:35:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}到底怎么啦？\N{\fs60}What the hell's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.84,0:35:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}结束啦！结束啦！\N{\fs60}It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.70,0:35:46.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}什么结束啦？\N{\fs60}What's over?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.50,0:35:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}妈的，冷战，苏联，邪恶帝国\N{\fs60}The Cold-fucking-War! The Soviet-fucking Union
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.98,0:35:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他说结束了\N{\fs60}The Evil fucking-Empire! Mikhail's saying no mas.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.32,0:35:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一切都结束了！\N{\fs60}He's throwing in the towel.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.55,0:35:53.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}都完了!\N{\fs60}It's over!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:57.55,0:35:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你儿子会走路了\N{\fs60}Your son is walking.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.41,0:36:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真棒，甜心\N{\fs60}That's incredible, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.15,0:36:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}起码他会给宗教自由\N{\fs60}At least they'll get religious freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.65,0:36:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}希望如此\N{\fs60}Let's hope so.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.07,0:36:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想回去看看\N{\fs60}I think I'll go back for a visit.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.82,0:36:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你和狄米奇叔叔还有连络吗？\N{\fs60}Do you stay in touch with Uncle Dmitri?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.62,0:36:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不是傻瓜，尤里\N{\fs60}I'm not a fool, Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.44,0:36:26.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不信你回去，是要卖百事可乐\N{\fs60}I don't think you're going to Odessa to sell Pepsi-Cola.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.35,0:36:32.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是你希望被后人纪念的方式吗？\N{\fs60}Is this how you want to be remembered?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.65,0:36:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我根本不希望留名青史\N{\fs60}I don't want to be remembered at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.62,0:36:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果是那样，就表示我已经死了\N{\fs60}I'm being remembered, it means I'm dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.60,0:36:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}圣诞快乐\N{\fs60}Merry-fucking-Christmas!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.84,0:36:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}维塔利，这是谁？\N{\fs60}Who is this, Vitaly?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.98,0:36:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我叫天使\N{\fs60}I'm Angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.78,0:36:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她真的是天使\N{\fs60}Her name really is Angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.49,0:36:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她真是\N{\fs60}She's a fairy.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.37,0:36:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}让我把她放在圣诞树顶\N{\fs60}Let's put her on top of the Christmas tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.04,0:36:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}来\N{\fs60}Come on
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.14,0:37:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我爱你\N{\fs60}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.47,0:37:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}来\N{\fs60}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.71,0:37:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我爱你们\N{\fs60}I love you all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.57,0:37:10.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}拿着\N{\fs60}Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.84,0:37:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我要回乌克兰\N{\fs60}I'm going back to Ukraine.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.26,0:37:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想念奥德萨\N{\fs60}I miss Odessa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.11,0:37:46.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想你\N{\fs60}I miss you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.34,0:37:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我也想你\N{\fs60}I miss you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.46,0:37:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}小心啊，尤里 你卖的东西是可以杀人的\N{\fs60}Be careful, Yuri. Those things you sell kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.06,0:37:56.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你的心\N{\fs60}Inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.97,0:38:01.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你过度紧张了\N{\fs60}You're high.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.73,0:38:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}也许吧\N{\fs60}That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.26,0:38:08.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}嗨，克里斯丁\N{\fs60}Hello, Christian.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.10,0:38:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(1036,892.6)}乌克兰，奥德萨 - 1992
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.78,0:38:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}冷战时期 因为是战略要地\N{\fs60}During the Cold War, the Red Army stationed nearly one million troops in Ukraine
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.06,0:38:23.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}红军在乌克兰屯兵百万\N{\fs60}because of its strategic military importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.38,0:38:26.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}柏林围墙倒后\N{\fs60}The day after The Wall came down...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.17,0:38:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}军人就领不到薪水了\N{\fs60}the paychecks stopped coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.86,0:38:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}你的证件
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.52,0:38:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}愤怒的士兵和满仓库的武器对军火贩来说\N{\fs60}There's nothing better for an arms dealer combination of disgruntled soldiers
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.34,0:38:35.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真是美妙的组合\N{\fs60}and warehouses full of weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.29,0:38:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}欢迎
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.75,0:38:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我寄望狄米奇将军\N{\fs60}I was hoping Major General Dmitri Volkoff
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.13,0:38:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}会打开各处军事基地的\N{\fs60}would open a lot of armory doors
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.86,0:38:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}武器仓库\N{\fs60}in a lot of military bases.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.95,0:38:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}首先，起码他是我家人\N{\fs60}For a start, he was family.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.15,0:38:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他是红军极力吹捧的英雄\N{\fs60}He was a highly decorated hero of the Red Army,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.69,0:38:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在却弄得脸上无光\N{\fs60}and he was almost permanently shit-faced
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.35,0:38:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不能私下卖政府的资产给你\N{\fs60}I can't just sell you government property, Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.45,0:38:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我得向上级汇报\N{\fs60}I have to report.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.15,0:39:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}向谁汇报？莫斯科？\N{\fs60}Report to who? Moscow?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.41,0:39:05.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}上周开始\N{\fs60}As of last week
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.26,0:39:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}莫斯科已经在外国了\N{\fs60}Moscow's in a foreign country.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.10,0:39:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}新国旗，新领导\N{\fs60}New flag, new boss.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.45,0:39:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}新领导还没产生呢\N{\fs60}There is no new boss yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.45,0:39:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们正忙着争夺\N{\fs60}They're all too busy squabbling over
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.32,0:39:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}黑海边的总统度假别墅\N{\fs60}who's gonna get the presidential holiday home at the Black Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.25,0:39:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它真豪华\N{\fs60}It's beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.02,0:39:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你所熟悉的领导已经不管事了\N{\fs60}The ones who know don't care any more
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.91,0:39:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那些管事的却什么也不知道\N{\fs60}and the ones who care don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.91,0:39:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}让我看看你的库存\N{\fs60}Show me your inventory.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.75,0:39:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}东西方45年来的敌对\N{\fs60}Those 45 years of mutual hatred between the East and the West
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.37,0:39:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}造就了历史上 最强大的武器\N{\fs60}had generated the highest weapons buildup in history.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.65,0:39:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}苏联有从地狱弄来的枪堆得比山高\N{\fs60}The Soviets had guns coming out of the demon hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:48.46,0:39:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在却没有敌人\N{\fs60}Huge stockpiles, and now no enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:52.55,0:39:54.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}总共多少支枪？\N{\fs60}How many Kalashnikovs do you have?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.12,0:39:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}四万\N{\fs60}Forty thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.42,0:40:00.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有四万？\N{\fs60}Is that a four?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.28,0:40:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我觉得不到四万\N{\fs60}It doesn't look like a four to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.88,0:40:04.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}看起来只有一万\N{\fs60}It's more like a one.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.15,0:40:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}的确有四万\N{\fs60}No, it's a four.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.48,0:40:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们说多少就是多少\N{\fs60}It's whatever we say it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.02,0:40:09.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谁也不知道有差\N{\fs60}Because no one else will know the difference?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.10,0:40:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一个营才有一万支枪\N{\fs60}Ten thousand Kalashnikovs for a Your stocks are battalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.22,0:40:19.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你的库存少得危险\N{\fs60}Your stocks are dangerously depleted, Dmitri.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.05,0:40:21.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你该去向工厂订货了\N{\fs60}You should order more from the factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.02,0:40:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有人会追查的\N{\fs60}Someone will work it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.50,0:40:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那时怎么办？\N{\fs60}What happens then?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.92,0:40:28.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}把他也拉进来\N{\fs60}We'll cut them in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.28,0:40:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}冷战结束时\N{\fs60}The end of the Cold War
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.62,0:40:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}却是军火交易最热络的时候\N{\fs60}was the beginning of the hottest time in arms dealing.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.42,0:40:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}军火市场开了大门\N{\fs60}The arms bazaar was open.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.15,0:40:41.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}导弹，非导弹\N{\fs60}Guided missiles, unguided missiles.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.55,0:40:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}迫击炮，地雷\N{\fs60}Mortars, mines,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.93,0:40:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}人员运输车\N{\fs60}armored personnel carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.66,0:40:46.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}整个部队的坦克\N{\fs60}Whole tank divisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.92,0:40:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}这样吧
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.21,0:40:50.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}买六送一
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.68,0:40:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我甚至还遇到一批 攻击直升机的火炮手\N{\fs60}I even landed a squadron of helicopter gunships.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.43,0:41:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}最精准的火炮\N{\fs60}The most sophisticated fighting machines...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.96,0:41:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为对付美国而造的 但战争却从未发生\N{\fs60}built for a war with America that never happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.11,0:41:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}小伙子，快下来吧 免得弄伤自己咯
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.32,0:41:18.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}我闭着眼睛都能把它拆了
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.68,0:41:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们得感谢我\N{\fs60}Thanks to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.59,0:41:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}终于有了 发炮的机会来发泄愤怒\N{\fs60}they'd finally get to fire a shot in anger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.33,0:41:34.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我有种感觉这大概不是列宁\N{\fs60}I have a feeling it wasn't exactly what Comrade Lenin had in mind
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.29,0:41:36.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当年所倡导的财产重新分配\N{\fs60}when he advocated the redistribution of wealth.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.64,0:41:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但我不是唯一的提供他们资本主义速成课程的人\N{\fs60}But I wasn't the only one offering a crash course in capitalism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.28,0:41:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我有竞争对手\N{\fs60}I had rivals.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.35,0:41:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}请通报指挥官\N{\fs60}Inform your commanding officer
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.97,0:41:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}席米恩·怀斯求见\N{\fs60}that Simeon Weisz is here to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.22,0:41:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不认识我吧？\N{\fs60}You don't know who I am, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.86,0:41:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}我管你是哪棵葱！
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.34,0:42:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你迟到了\N{\fs60}You're late.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.73,0:42:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}似乎是\N{\fs60}So it appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.93,0:42:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}谢谢
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.14,0:42:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(954,900.7)}不客气
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.77,0:42:27.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(962,900.7)}你是卖枪的？
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.15,0:42:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(936,833.2)}或许你可以来我房间 我让你瞧瞧我的
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.90,0:42:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(958,889.9)}火炮
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.08,0:42:41.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}看上去你似乎摸不着门路\N{\fs60}You look a little lost, Simeon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.54,0:42:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是世界改变得太快了吗？\N{\fs60}Is the world changing too fast?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:43.68,0:42:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我这不是找来了吗？\N{\fs60}I'm here, aren't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.47,0:42:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不全然\N{\fs60}Not all of you, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.22,0:42:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你替中情局贩卖军火赚了大钱\N{\fs60}You've gotten so rich selling for the CIA
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.98,0:42:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但你似乎还无法\N{\fs60}you can't seem to get that ideology
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.64,0:42:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}放下身段\N{\fs60}completely out of your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.97,0:42:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}冷战时我不得不如此\N{\fs60}Oh, the Cold War had its uses.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.13,0:42:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}得首先考虑双方紧张的关系\N{\fs60}Kept the tensions frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.26,0:43:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在很难取舍\N{\fs60}Now it's harder to determine
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.39,0:43:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}该站在哪一方\N{\fs60}which side one's on.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.90,0:43:04.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}事情变得比较复杂了\N{\fs60}Things have become more complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.98,0:43:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不，是变简单了\N{\fs60}No, it's gotten simpler.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.10,0:43:10.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}政治考量已经不存在于军火业了\N{\fs60}There's no place in gunrunning for politics anymore,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.31,0:43:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我卖给左翼，也卖给右翼\N{\fs60}I sell to leftists and rightists.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.92,0:43:14.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}甚至和平主义者\N{\fs60}I sell to pacifists,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.22,0:43:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不过他们不是常客啦\N{\fs60}but they're not the most regular of customers.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.31,0:43:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你如果不卖武器\N{\fs60}Of course, you're not a true internationalist...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.06,0:43:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}去打击自己的国家\N{\fs60}...until you've supplied weapons
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.49,0:43:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你就算不上是个国际军火贩\N{\fs60}to kill your own countrymen.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.40,0:43:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现今这种混乱的局势不能继续下去\N{\fs60}This current state of chaos won't last forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:29.26,0:43:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}必须重新建立秩序\N{\fs60}There'll have to be order.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.48,0:43:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}与其互相敌对\N{\fs60}Instead of cutting each other's throats,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.12,0:43:38.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}咱们不如合作\N{\fs60}it may be beneficial if we work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:38.31,0:43:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如何？\N{\fs60}What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.57,0:43:43.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我认为如何？\N{\fs60}What do I think?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.02,0:43:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我认为你现在才是玩票的\N{\fs60}I think you are the amateur now,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.65,0:43:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你应该按照你的直觉去做\N{\fs60}and I think you should go with your instincts.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.87,0:43:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你的第一个直觉\N{\fs60}With your first instinct.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.94,0:43:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}过去的我不配给你提鞋\N{\fs60}I'm the same man who was not good enough for you before
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.87,0:43:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在还是不配\N{\fs60}and I'm just not good enough for you now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.45,0:44:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}军火贩子之间开战有个麻烦\N{\fs60}The problem with gunrunners going to war
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.50,0:44:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就是双方都有用不尽的弹药\N{\fs60}is that there's no shortage of ammunition.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.09,0:44:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这就是咱们这行老前辈们总在顾忌的\N{\fs60}This was the chaos that the Old Guard had always feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.06,0:44:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们担心 我会搞坏军火商的名声\N{\fs60}As far as they were concerned,I was giving arms dealers a bad name.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.70,0:44:32.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是他们无法向优化商务局举报我\N{\fs60}But they could hardly report me to the Better Business Bureau.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.92,0:44:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}乌克兰不是唯一一个\N{\fs60}And Ukraine wasn't the only former state...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.41,0:44:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}拥有没有工资的军队和很多军火的国家\N{\fs60}with an unpaid army and stockpiles of guns.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:40.48,0:44:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这里还有保加利亚，匈牙利 波兰，巴拉如斯\N{\fs60}There was Bulgaria, Hungary, Poland, Belarus...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:45.34,0:44:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们全都是\N{\fs60}all there for the taking.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.53,0:44:54.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在苏联兵工厂里的所有武器中\N{\fs60}Of all the weapons in the vast Soviet arsenal...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.61,0:44:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没有一种像AK47\N{\fs60}nothing was more profitable than Avtomat Kalashnikova,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:58.11,0:44:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}或者叫卡拉希尼可夫\N{\fs60}model of 1947,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.89,0:45:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}更赚钱的\N{\fs60}more commonly known as the AK-47... or kalashnikov.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.08,0:45:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它是世界上最流行的冲锋枪\N{\fs60}It's the world's most popular assault rifle
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.00,0:45:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}战士最喜爱的武器\N{\fs60}a weapon all fighters love.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:09.18,0:45:13.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}由9磅金属和4英尺长木头制成\N{\fs60}An elegantly simple nine-pound amalgamation of forged steel and plywood.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.62,0:45:16.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它不会坏，卡壳，或者过热\N{\fs60}It doesn't break, jam, or overheat.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:16.40,0:45:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就算它被泥土或者沙子覆盖还是可以正常的开火\N{\fs60}It will shoot whether it's covered in mud or filled with sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.70,0:45:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它的使用非常简单 就算一个小孩都可以使用它\N{\fs60}It's so easy, even a child can use it
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.31,0:45:23.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}而且他们的确在使用它\N{\fs60}and they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.49,0:45:25.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}苏联把枪放到他们的钱币上\N{\fs60}The Soviets put the gun on a coin.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.60,0:45:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}莫桑比克把枪的图案放在国旗上\N{\fs60}Mozambique put it on their flag.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.09,0:45:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}自从冷战结束后\N{\fs60}Since the end of the Cold War,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.61,0:45:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}AK47成为了苏联主要的出口货物\N{\fs60}the Kalashnikov has become the Russian people's greatest export.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.35,0:45:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}接着是伏特加酒，鱼子酱\N{\fs60}After that comes vodka, caviar,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:35.52,0:45:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}和有自杀倾向的诗人\N{\fs60}and suicidal novelists.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:38.02,0:45:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有一点我确定\N{\fs60}One thing's for sure
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.35,0:45:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没有人想排队去买他们的车\N{\fs60}no one was lining up to buy their cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.65,0:45:58.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(962,900.7)}他娘的什么文件
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.99,0:46:05.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(962,900.7)}听我说，中尉
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.78,0:46:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(962,900.7)}把他们留在那里，越长越好
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.66,0:46:11.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(958,1068.1)}战斗到死\N\N\N\N\N莫斯科支持我们
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.79,0:46:13.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(962,900.7)}这是我的命令
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.86,0:46:14.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我以为你应该躲着这些人\N{\fs60}I thought you supposed watching out for these people.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.97,0:46:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我怎么躲\N{\fs60}How can I?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.47,0:46:18.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不停卖我的直升机\N{\fs60}You keep selling my helicopters.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.41,0:46:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你太贪钱了，尤里\N{\fs60}You are too greedy, Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.24,0:46:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不能永远的挡住他\N{\fs60}I can't hold him forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.33,0:46:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我有许可书\N{\fs60}I've got paperwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.54,0:46:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}对战斗直升机无效\N{\fs60}Not for the gunships.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.32,0:46:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你知道如果我们被抓了\N{\fs60}You know the penalty for sanction-busting.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.94,0:46:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}卖军用直升机可是一项重罪\N{\fs60}Selling the military helicopter is a major violation.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.12,0:46:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}军用直升机\N{\fs60}Military helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.02,0:46:38.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这不是一架军用直升机\N{\fs60}It's not a military helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.14,0:46:40.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是一架救援直升机\N{\fs60}It's a rescue helicopter.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.52,0:46:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}快干活，小子\N{\fs60}Get to work, son.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.90,0:46:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(956,898)}没问题
Dialogue: 0,0:46:46.20,0:46:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}法律在我们这边\N{\fs60}The law's on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.41,0:47:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好的，让我看一看你的许可书\N{\fs60}All right, let me see your papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.26,0:47:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不要，把枪拿开\N{\fs60}No-no-no, put that away.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.66,0:47:12.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}让我看一看你的许可书\N{\fs60}See your papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:12.96,0:47:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里·奥洛夫\N{\fs60}Yuri Orlov.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.84,0:47:17.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}奥洛夫先生总是在正确的时间 出现在错误的地方\N{\fs60}Mr. Orlov, always In the wrong place at the right time.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.77,0:47:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(956,898)}这到底是怎么回事？
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.64,0:47:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们以前见过\N{\fs60}We've met before.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.01,0:47:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在哥伦比亚的海岸线附近\N{\fs60}Off the coast Colombia.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.01,0:47:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那船叫什么名字来着?\N{\fs60}What was the name of that freighter?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:25.46,0:47:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}柯诺号还是克里斯多号?\N{\fs60}I can't remember, was it the Kono or the Kristol?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.68,0:47:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}船上的船员给那艘船起了很多名字\N{\fs60}The crew called that vessel a lot of names.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.06,0:47:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没有一个是好名字\N{\fs60}None repeatable in polite company.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.89,0:47:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}回答你的问题\N{\fs60}Answer the question.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.39,0:47:36.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}哦，新型的MP5\N{\fs60}The new MP-5.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.98,0:47:38.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你想要个消音器吗？\N{\fs60}Would you like a silencer for that?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.84,0:47:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我要看你的许可证\N{\fs60}I need to see your papers.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.04,0:47:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fs75\pos(956,898)}离我远一点
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.27,0:47:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}狄米奇\N{\fs60}Dmitri!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.74,0:47:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这架直升机的使用者证明书上写着\N{\fs60}The end-user certificate for this aircraft...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.99,0:47:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}沃克纳·瓦梢\N{\fs60}states "Burkina Faso."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.63,0:47:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真不错\N{\fs60}Nice, very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.54,0:47:56.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是你自己打的吗？\N{\fs60}Did you type this up yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.81,0:47:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这架直升机是用来执行人道主义任务的\N{\fs60}The helicopter is to be used on humanitarian missions.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.39,0:48:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}噢，你是一个人道主义者\N{\fs60}Oh, so you're a humanitarian?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:01.36,0:48:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当然是\N{\fs60}Oh, absolutely.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.50,0:48:05.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是一架军用直升机\N{\fs60}This is a military aircraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.25,0:48:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在不是了 - 听他讲\N{\fs60}Not anymore. - Listen to the nephew!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.14,0:48:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们能用由军用直升机 改装的民用直升机做什么\N{\fs60}What can they do with military hardware but convert it to civilian use?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.84,0:48:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果是因为这架直升机死了人\N{\fs60}The only way you could die from this baby
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.72,0:48:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那是因为你被投掷的食物砸死了\N{\fs60}now is if a food drop hits you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.91,0:48:19.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这边的东西呢？\N{\fs60}And this stuff over here, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.16,0:48:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们也用来行人道主义任务吗？\N{\fs60}Is it going to Burkina Faso... Ah,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.32,0:48:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不同的客户，不同的地址\N{\fs60}but to a different client at a different address.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.30,0:48:24.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}只是一个巧合是吗？\N{\fs60}That's just a coincidence is that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.99,0:48:27.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你以为我是一个大傻瓜吗？\N{\fs60}Do you take me for a complete fucking fool?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.58,0:48:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}并不是很傻\N{\fs60}Not complete, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.19,0:48:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不会打搅你的工作\N{\fs60}And while I hesitate to tell your job.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.36,0:48:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我必须指出\N{\fs60}I must point out that when shipped separately,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.82,0:48:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果我分开运输武器和直升机\N{\fs60}the weapons and the aircraft both comply with current Interpol
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.38,0:48:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}都符合现在的国际条约\N{\fs60}trade standards and practices.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.01,0:48:38.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们都知道\N{\fs60}We both know,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.77,0:48:42.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这只是一个条约上的漏洞\N{\fs60}that is an obscene bureaucratic loophole that's gonna be closed
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.55,0:48:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这个漏洞不知那天就会消失\N{\fs60}any goddamn day.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.89,0:48:45.18,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是现在还没消失\N{\fs60}But it's not closed.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.82,0:48:48.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有些人也许认为 这些集装箱可疑\N{\fs60}And while certain people might interpret this cargo as suspicious,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:49.17,0:48:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}感谢上帝 只有可疑是无法给我定罪的\N{\fs60}thank God we live in a world, where suspicion alone does not constitute a crime.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.91,0:48:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}像你这样的人\N{\fs60}And men like you
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.22,0:48:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}会遵守法律条约\N{\fs60}respect the rule of law.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.77,0:49:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的确是有罪的\N{\fs60}I was as guilty as sin,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.41,0:49:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是瓦伦丁无法证明\N{\fs60}but Valentine couldn't prove it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:04.12,0:49:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他是执法人员里很少见的\N{\fs60}And he was the rarest breed of law enforcement officer,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:06.86,0:49:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尽管他知道我在犯法\N{\fs60}the type who knew I was breaking the law,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.78,0:49:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是他不会以非法的手段来逮捕我\N{\fs60}but wouldn't break it himself to bust me.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.17,0:49:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(336,908.8)}两天后
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.91,0:49:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}瓦伦丁并不是唯一想让我没生意做的人\N{\fs60}Valentine wasn't the only one trying to put me out of business.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.98,0:49:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}狄米奇拒绝了许多其他的军火商\N{\fs60}My uncle had turned down a half dozen rival arms dealers,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:21.02,0:49:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有时他们的条件比我的要好\N{\fs60}sometimes with offers better than mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.57,0:49:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是你不能用钱来买衷心\N{\fs60}But to Dmitri, you couldn't put a price on loyalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.88,0:49:40.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他来这干什么？\N{\fs60}What was he doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.97,0:49:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他希望能抢到你的生意\N{\fs60}He is hoping to beat your offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.84,0:49:45.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我告诉他去死吧\N{\fs60}I told him to go have intercourse with himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.30,0:49:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是，尤里\N{\fs60}But Yuri
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.73,0:49:49.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你应该多给一些了\N{\fs60}You need to make more payoffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.43,0:49:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}很多人已经知道了 - 不用担心\N{\fs60}Too many know. - Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.06,0:49:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我放了很多录像机和烟\N{\fs60}There are more VCRs and cigarettes.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.75,0:49:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在你的新车里\N{\fs60}I left them in your new car.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.93,0:49:57.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就连你的敌人都很喜欢那辆车\N{\fs60}Even your enemy was admiring that car.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.82,0:50:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我是世界上最幸运的人\N{\fs60}I'm the luckiest man alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.14,0:50:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你的确是\N{\fs60}You are.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.14,0:50:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}喂\N{\fs60}Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.06,0:50:45.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}艾娃？\N{\fs60}Ava?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.80,0:50:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}亲爱的\N{\fs60}Hi, baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.69,0:50:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你知道现在几点了吗?\N{\fs60}You forgot what time it is?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.74,0:50:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}对不起...\N{\fs60}Sorry, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.74,0:50:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你的面试怎么样？\N{\fs60}How was that your audition?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.61,0:50:58.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们改变了他们的要求\N{\fs60}They're going in another direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.51,0:51:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们想要一个可以表演的人\N{\fs60}Direction with someone who can act.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.88,0:51:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们配不上你\N{\fs60}They don't deserve you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.34,0:51:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你在哪？\N{\fs60}Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.85,0:51:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一切都好吗？\N{\fs60}Is everything okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.42,0:51:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不是很好\N{\fs60}It was a rough day at the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.51,0:51:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}回家吧\N{\fs60}Come home.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.85,0:51:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}很快就回家了 尼克怎么样?\N{\fs60}Soon. How's Nicki?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.00,0:51:16.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他很想你 我们都想你\N{\fs60}He misses you. We both do.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.92,0:51:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们没有你感到很孤独\N{\fs60}It's lonely without you here.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.84,0:51:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你知道我不喜欢夜晚\N{\fs60}You know I don't like nights.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.05,0:51:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}自从我的父母...\N{\fs60}Ever since my parents...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.86,0:51:35.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里，那是什么声音？\N{\fs60}Yuri, what's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.96,0:51:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一个聚会\N{\fs60}A party.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.00,0:51:38.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我该走了\N{\fs60}I'd better go.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.10,0:51:40.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}只是想听一听你的声音\N{\fs60}Just wanted to call and hear your voice.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.18,0:51:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}替我亲一下尼克\N{\fs60}Kiss Nicki for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.23,0:51:42.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我爱你\N{\fs60}I love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.78,0:51:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}军火并没有因为狄米奇的死而消失\N{\fs60}The pillaging didn't die with my uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.93,0:51:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}自从墙倒塌后\N{\fs60}After The Wall came down
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.73,0:51:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}价值3200亿的军火\N{\fs60}$32 billion billion dollars worth of arms
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.44,0:51:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}被盗然后从乌克兰被买走\N{\fs60}were stolen and resold from Ukraine alone,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.03,0:51:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是20世纪最高的纪录\N{\fs60}one of the greatest heists of the 20th Century.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.93,0:52:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\bord0\shad4\fad(400,300)\fs75\pos(424,906.1)}蒙罗维亚, 利比里 - 1995
Dialogue: 0,0:52:12.93,0:52:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}非洲是最主要的市场\N{\fs60}The primary market was Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.33,0:52:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在10年里\N{\fs60}Eleven major conflicts involving
Dialogue: 0,0:52:17.29,0:52:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有11场战斗，23个国家参与\N{\fs60}thirty-two countries in less than a decade...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.46,0:52:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是军火走私商的天堂\N{\fs60}A gunrunner's wet dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.36,0:52:23.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在，西方并不关心这些\N{\fs60}At the time, the West couldn't care less.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.56,0:52:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}{\an7\fs60}注：波黑战争时期
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.56,0:52:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们在南斯拉夫有一场白人的战争要打\N{\fs60}They had a white war in what was left of Yugoslavia.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.93,0:52:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我最主要在利比里做我的生意\N{\fs60}I did the bulk of my business in Liberia...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.30,0:52:30.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}自由之地\N{\fs60}"Land of the Free."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.00,0:52:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一开始这里是黑人奴隶的自由之地\N{\fs60}Originally established as a homeland for freed American slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.74,0:52:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是从那之后这些奴隶还是被这个或者另一个人统治着\N{\fs60}it's been enslaved by one dictator or another ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.29,0:52:40.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}最新的统治者是受过美国教育的\N{\fs60}The latest was American-educated,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.02,0:52:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}自封为总统的安德烈·巴特思\N{\fs60}self declared president, Andre Baptiste.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.46,0:52:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里先生\N{\fs60}Mr. Yuri!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.76,0:52:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我是安德烈·巴特思二世\N{\fs60}I'm Andre Baptiste, Junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.43,0:52:57.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的父亲想见你\N{\fs60}My father would like to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:57.46,0:52:58.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真是荣幸\N{\fs60}What an honor.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.73,0:53:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谢谢\N{\fs60}Thank him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.57,0:53:02.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是我还有其他生意要做\N{\fs60}But unfortunately I have other business.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.79,0:53:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}对不起，我很忙\N{\fs60}It's a shame, it's a very busy schedule.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.86,0:53:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}应该说你没有选择的权利\N{\fs60}It is not, as they say, optional.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.52,0:53:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的父亲很容易生气\N{\fs60}My father is easily offended.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.36,0:53:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我突然有时间了\N{\fs60}My schedule just freed up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:27.27,0:53:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}巴布锑总统是我最好的客人\N{\fs60}President Baptiste was my best customer
Dialogue: 0,0:53:29.59,0:53:31.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是我不着急去见他\N{\fs60}but I was in no hurry to meet him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.48,0:53:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他消除异己的残忍手段路人皆知\N{\fs60}He'd gotten a reputation for routinely hacking off the limbs of those who opposed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.06,0:53:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}7年的内战\N{\fs60}His seven-year civil war has been described...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.74,0:53:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}被总结为纯粹为了暴力的战争\N{\fs60}as "a relentless campaign of sadistic wanton violence."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.79,0:53:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这就是我将要去见的安迪\N{\fs60}That kind of sums up Andy for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.03,0:53:49.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这个转轮很有趣\N{\fs60}The Glock is interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.03,0:53:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他是合金制成的\N{\fs60}It's made of a polymer composite.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.18,0:53:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这样过机场安检就不会触发警铃\N{\fs60}Many of my clients feel they can get through airport security without setting off a lot of bells and whistles.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.90,0:53:59.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是我并不同意这样做\N{\fs60}Personally I do not recommend that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.84,0:54:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}从另一方面来说\N{\fs60}On the other hand,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.54,0:54:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果你想要一种传统的大火力手枪\N{\fs60}if you are looking for a traditional wheel gun,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.11,0:54:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没有一种枪可以代替\N{\fs60}there is no substitute for the six inches
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.17,0:54:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}6英寸长的.357毫米马格南\N{\fs60}of muzzle energy of a.357 magnum.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.43,0:54:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当然它从不卡壳\N{\fs60}And of course, it will never jam.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.94,0:54:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你为什么这么做？\N{\fs60}Why did you do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.33,0:54:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你说什么？\N{\fs60}What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.29,0:54:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你必须买下它\N{\fs60}Now you'll have to buy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.47,0:54:21.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它已经被你用过了\N{\fs60}It's a used gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.66,0:54:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我怎么能卖掉用过的枪\N{\fs60}How can I sell a used gun?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.00,0:54:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一把用过的枪\N{\fs60}A used gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.50,0:54:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一把用过的枪\N{\fs60}A used gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.71,0:54:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有趣\N{\fs60}That's a good one.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.82,0:54:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你知道吗？现在的年轻人没有纪律\N{\fs60}You know there is no discipline with the youth today.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:41.56,0:54:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我只是想树立一个榜样 虽然这不容易\N{\fs60}I try to set an example but it is difficult, eh?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.31,0:54:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想这都是MTV的错\N{\fs60}Personally, I blame MTV.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.56,0:54:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一把用过的枪\N{\fs60}A used gun.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.40,0:55:02.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想我们可以做生意了\N{\fs60}I think you and I, we can do business.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.42,0:55:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果说我害怕安德烈一世\N{\fs60}If I thought I was scared of Andre Senior,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.86,0:55:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不如说我更害怕安德烈二世\N{\fs60}I knew I was scared of Andre Junior.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.71,0:55:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有其父必有其子\N{\fs60}Like father, like son.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.69,0:55:14.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就像果实从来不会掉到离树很远的地方\N{\fs60}The guava doesn't fall too far from the tree.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.79,0:55:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他简直是一个食人怪\N{\fs60}He was also a cannibal.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.65,0:55:18.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们说安德烈会吃掉\N{\fs60}They say Andre would eat a victim's heart
Dialogue: 0,0:55:18.61,0:55:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他的敌人还在跳动的心脏\N{\fs60}while it was still beating
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.98,0:55:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这样他可以得到超越常人的力量\N{\fs60}to give him superhuman strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.35,0:55:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}到蒙罗维亚就像到了另一个星球一样\N{\fs60}Monrovia itself was like being on another planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.89,0:55:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}蒙罗维亚星球\N{\fs60}Planet Monrovia.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.93,0:55:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}从气温来说\N{\fs60}From the temperature,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:35.78,0:55:38.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它是最接近太阳的星球\N{\fs60}it was obviously a planet close to the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.42,0:55:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我从没见过另一个白人\N{\fs60}I rarely saw another white man,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.32,0:55:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我从来不独自离开这个村庄\N{\fs60}and I never left town alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.16,0:55:45.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这个村庄之外就是地狱的边缘\N{\fs60}Outside town was the edge of hell.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:45.51,0:55:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我连看都不想看\N{\fs60}I didn't want to even gaze into it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.75,0:55:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这就是你住的旅馆 2星级的\N{\fs60}This is your hotel. Two stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.72,0:55:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你能带给我蓝博之枪吗？\N{\fs60}Can you bring me the gun of Rambo?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.81,0:55:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}第1，2，还是第3集的？\N{\fs60}Part one, two, or three?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.95,0:55:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我只看过第一集\N{\fs60}I've only seen part one.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.42,0:56:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}M60\N{\fs60}The M-60.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.56,0:56:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你想要带穿甲弹的吗？\N{\fs60}Would you like the armor-piercing bullets?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.52,0:56:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}太好了\N{\fs60}Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.24,0:56:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我父亲留了一个见面礼在你房间里\N{\fs60}My father left a welcoming present in your room.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.81,0:56:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}慢慢享受吧\N{\fs60}Enjoy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.85,0:56:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的天啊，她差点就被砍头了\N{\fs60}My God, she nearly got her head cut off.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:30.00,0:56:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当我到美国时\N{\fs60}When I get to America,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.80,0:56:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不会住在那里\N{\fs60}I will not live in Brentwood.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.28,0:56:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}2楼\N{\fs60}Second floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:41.56,0:56:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在全球艾滋病最流行的地方\N{\fs60}In the most AIDS-infested region of the globe...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.28,0:56:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}4人中就有1人感染\N{\fs60}where one in four is infected...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.62,0:56:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}安德烈和我开玩笑的方式\N{\fs60}Andre's idea of a joke was to put
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.54,0:56:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就是把两个漂亮的女人放到我床上\N{\fs60}a young lman and a young Naomi in my bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.29,0:56:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}而且在方圆100英里内找不到避孕套\N{\fs60}And no condom within 100 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.35,0:57:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你好，尤里先生\N{\fs60}Hello, Mr. Yuri.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.30,0:57:12.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好\N{\fs60}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.59,0:57:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们很高兴可以使你感觉高兴\N{\fs60}We'd be happy to make you happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.66,0:57:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不能，我想要做\N{\fs60}Uh, I can't. I'd love to.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.46,0:57:22.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是我不能\N{\fs60}But I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.18,0:57:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不要担心\N{\fs60}Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.66,0:57:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们没有病\N{\fs60}We don't have anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.35,0:57:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你怎么知道？\N{\fs60}How do you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.27,0:57:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们看起来像有病吗？\N{\fs60}Do we look like it?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.26,0:57:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果我有艾滋病呢？\N{\fs60}What if I have AIDS?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.12,0:57:40.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不担心吗？\N{\fs60}Don't you worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.73,0:57:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你担心的太多了\N{\fs60}You worry too much.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:44.59,0:57:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为什么你现在担心一个\N{\fs60}Why do you worry about something that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:46.45,0:57:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}10年后才会杀死你的病\N{\fs60}can kill you in ten years
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.81,0:57:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}今天就有很多机会你会死\N{\fs60}when there are so many things that can kill you today?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.99,0:57:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}现在\N{\fs60}Now...
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.02,0:58:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们如何才能使你高兴\N{\fs60}...how can we make you happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.26,0:58:04.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}离开这里\N{\fs60}By leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.72,0:58:12.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这些武装到牙齿的儿童\N{\fs60}These are my Kalashnikov Kids.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.02,0:58:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的童子军\N{\fs60}My Boy Brigades.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.59,0:58:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我知道你在想什么\N{\fs60}I can see what you are thinking,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.36,0:58:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是我们需要所有我们可以用的上的男性\N{\fs60}but we need every man we can get.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.99,0:58:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}即使他们还没有长大？\N{\fs60}Even if they're not men?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.08,0:58:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}从14岁孩子的枪里射出的子弹\N{\fs60}A bullet from a fourteen-year-old...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.80,0:58:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}就像从40岁男人的枪里射出的子弹一样致命\N{\fs60}...is just as effective as one from a forty-year-old.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.76,0:58:30.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}也许更致命\N{\fs60}Often more effective.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.11,0:58:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}没有人可以阻止这场血浴之战\N{\fs60}No one can stop this bath of blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.65,0:58:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不是血浴之战\N{\fs60}It's not "bath of blood."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.71,0:58:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是浴血之战\N{\fs60}It's "bloodbath."
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.46,0:58:41.30,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谢谢\N{\fs60}Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:42.42,0:58:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但是我喜欢这么说\N{\fs60}But I prefer it my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.02,0:58:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不会给你出的价钱\N{\fs60}I am not going to pay your asking price.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.40,0:59:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们并不富有\N{\fs60}We are not a rich people. And besides,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.70,0:59:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}而且市场上已经充斥着你的枪\N{\fs60}the market is already flooded with your Kalashnikovs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.03,0:59:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你知道在这个国家的某些地方\N{\fs60}Do you realize in some parts of my country
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.28,0:59:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你可以用一只鸡换一只枪\N{\fs60}you can get one for the price of a chicken?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.03,0:59:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你不能只看单价\N{\fs60}But you can't just consider unit price.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.96,0:59:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还有其他辅助费用\N{\fs60}You forget ancillary costs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.44,0:59:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}伪造文件\N{\fs60}End-user certificates need to be forged and notarized,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.93,0:59:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}建立空壳公司\N{\fs60}Shell companies set up,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.05,0:59:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}买保险，还有请临时工\N{\fs60}insurance purchased, pilots and crews hired.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:18.30,0:59:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}贿赂别人的钱也很多\N{\fs60}Not to mention bribes.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.16,0:59:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不贿赂别人\N{\fs60}You can't get a nut and bolt out
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.67,0:59:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你根本无法进入边界\N{\fs60}of the Eastern Bloc without a bribe.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:23.28,0:59:24.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}给那个疯子一笔贿赂\N{\fs60}There's one bribe for the nut,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.66,0:59:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还有一笔要给那个秃子\N{\fs60}another for the bolt.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.28,0:59:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}安迪，安迪 听我说\N{\fs60}Andy... Andy, listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.71,0:59:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这是一个很费钱的生意\N{\fs60}This is an expensive proposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.08,0:59:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}“安迪”？\N{\fs60}"Andy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.22,0:59:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我会付你木材或者钻石\N{\fs60}I am going to pay you in timber or stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.02,0:59:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我当然选钻石\N{\fs60}I'll take the stones.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.61,0:59:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我可不能把一棵树装进我的手提箱里\N{\fs60}It's kind of hard to get a tree trunk into my hand luggage.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.63,0:59:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我知道你在计划反击\N{\fs60}I know you're planning a new offensive.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.09,0:59:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}如果你能推迟计划一周\N{\fs60}If you can delay a week,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.86,0:59:54.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我可以给你装甲车\N{\fs60}I can get you armored personnel carriers.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.24,0:59:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}它可以有效的减少你的伤亡人数\N{\fs60}They'd greatly reduce your casualties...
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.73,1:00:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还可以给你在战场上的优势\N{\fs60}...and give you a significant strategic advantage.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.55,1:00:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你知道他们叫我战争之王\N{\fs60}You know, they call me the Lord Of War.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.90,1:00:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想你才是\N{\fs60}But perhaps it is you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.60,1:00:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不是战争之王，应该叫军阀\N{\fs60}It's not "Lord Of War," it's "Warlord."
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.30,1:00:15.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谢谢，但是我喜欢这么说\N{\fs60}Thank you, but I prefer it my way.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.30,1:00:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}钻石在西非是最常用的货币\N{\fs60}Conflict diamonds are a common currency in West Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.72,1:00:24.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}也叫做血之钻石\N{\fs60}also referred to as "blood diamonds"
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.98,1:00:27.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}因为这些钻石往往都被用于资助流血战争\N{\fs60}since bloodshed is what they generally finance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.99,1:00:31.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}在20世纪末期\N{\fs60}By the late '90s, my wealth had caught up
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.06,1:00:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我的财富已经和我说谎时讲的差不多了\N{\fs60}to my lies about my welth.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.81,1:00:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}也许比我说谎时讲的还要多\N{\fs60}Even surpassed my lies.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:34.85,1:00:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我甚至有财力去收藏艺术品\N{\fs60}I could even afford to become a patron of the arts.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.56,1:00:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}哇，真不敢相信\N{\fs60}It's just that I can't believe it.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.87,1:00:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}这当然很棒\N{\fs60}Well, of... of course, it's wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.07,1:00:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我只是...\N{\fs60}I just...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.03,1:00:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}只是没想到这么快发生\N{\fs60}I didn't expect it to happen so soon.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.91,1:00:59.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是...那...也很好\N{\fs60}Yes. Well, that wou-that would be great, too yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.81,1:01:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}太好了，真谢谢你\N{\fs60}It's wonderful. Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.22,1:01:07.33,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是...尤里...好...谢谢...再见\N{\fs60}It's... Yuri. Okay, thank you. Bye.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.39,1:01:09.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}刚电话里是那个艺术商\N{\fs60}Yuri, that was the dealer on the phone.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.18,1:01:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我卖了第一张画\N{\fs60}I just sold my first painting.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:10.50,1:01:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}哇，真是太棒了\N{\fs60}Aah! That's fantastic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.89,1:01:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}谁买了？\N{\fs60}Uh, who bought it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:15.23,1:01:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}一位要人\N{\fs60}It's someone important.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.74,1:01:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不愿透漏姓名\N{\fs60}They want to remain anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:18.30,1:01:20.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真棒！ -对呀！这次外出都好吗？\N{\fs60}This is so wonderful! - How was your trip?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:20.59,1:01:21.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}哦...差不多啦...\N{\fs60}You know, same old, same old.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.81,1:01:22.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尼奇呢？\N{\fs60}Where's Nicki?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.99,1:01:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他睡了，撑不住了\N{\fs60}Oh, in bed, I'm sorry. He couldn't stay up.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.62,1:01:26.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}不要紧\N{\fs60}That's best.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.54,1:01:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}第一副画耶！\N{\fs60}My first painting!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.26,1:01:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我正式成为艺术家啦！\N{\fs60}I'm officially an artist!
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.98,1:01:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}值得干一杯 -谁说不是？\N{\fs60}This calls for a drink.  - What doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.99,1:01:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好\N{\fs60}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.68,1:01:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里，这是...呃...\N{\fs60}Yuri, this is uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.74,1:01:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}小蜜糖\N{\fs60}Candy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:38.67,1:01:40.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}小蜜糖！当然咯！\N{\fs60}Candy. Of course.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.48,1:01:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我弟弟的朋友都是...\N{\fs60}Any friend of my brother's is a...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.38,1:01:45.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我弟弟的朋友\N{\fs60}friend of my brother's.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:45.88,1:01:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好漂亮哦！你的...一切\N{\fs60}You have a beautiful... everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.98,1:01:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他当然是\N{\fs60}Yes, he does.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.45,1:01:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}是...我当然是\N{\fs60}Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:53.84,1:01:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我要去看看尼奇\N{\fs60}I'm going to kiss Nicki goodnight.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.52,1:02:52.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}老弟，还好吗？\N{\fs60}How are you, brother?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.85,1:02:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你知道的...\N{\fs60}Well, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.55,1:02:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我是家里的败类\N{\fs60}still the resident family fuckup.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.40,1:03:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}嗯...呃...总得有一个吧\N{\fs60}Yeah. Well, I guess someone has to do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.02,1:03:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}恩\N{\fs60}Well.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.46,1:03:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}艾娃知道你在干嘛，对吧？\N{\fs60}Hey, Ava knows, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.02,1:03:14.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我可不想说\N{\fs60}I never want to say anything,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.83,1:03:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她不需要了解 她懂的\N{\fs60}She doesn't have to know. She understands.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:16.98,1:03:19.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她是一个幸存者，跟我一样\N{\fs60}She's a survivor, like me.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.33,1:03:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她也许是\N{\fs60}She may be a survivor,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:21.79,1:03:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}但她绝对跟你不一样\N{\fs60}but she's not like you.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.52,1:03:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她不知道你怎么负担得起这一切\N{\fs60}Really She doesn't know how you pay for all this
Dialogue: 0,1:03:28.59,1:03:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我们从不提这事儿\N{\fs60}We don't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.08,1:03:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}卖车的会告诉你车有危险？\N{\fs60}How many car salesman talk about their work? Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:34.51,1:03:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}卖香烟的会吗？ 每年他们的商品\N{\fs60}How many cigarette salesmen? Both their products kill more people
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.39,1:03:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}比我的枪害死更多人\N{\fs60}every year than mine.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.37,1:03:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}起码我的商品还有安全栓呢\N{\fs60}At least mine has a safety switch.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.72,1:03:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}那些人不会把工作上的事带回家\N{\fs60}If those guys can leave their work at the office,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.41,1:03:45.42,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我也不会\N{\fs60}so can I.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.40,1:03:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}天啊...妈的...你真行！\N{\fs60}God damn, you are good!
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.14,1:03:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}真的\N{\fs60}You really are.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.06,1:03:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你差点让我相信了\N{\fs60}You almost had me convinced.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.61,1:04:09.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}你能...\N{\fs60}Could you...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.83,1:04:13.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}帮帮我吗？\N{\fs60}could you help me out with...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.14,1:04:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为什么？\N{\fs60}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:23.58,1:04:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}什么？\N{\fs60}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.22,1:04:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为什么？\N{\fs60}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.40,1:04:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}什么为什么？\N{\fs60}Why what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:30.34,1:04:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为什么？\N{\fs60}Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.45,1:04:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为什么？- 我不知道\N{\fs60}Why? I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:32.41,1:04:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为什么？-  我不知道\N{\fs60}Why... I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.71,1:04:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}什么？\N{\fs60}Why what?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:36.56,1:04:38.56,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}为什么你老闯祸？\N{\fs60}Why're you so fucked up all the time?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.37,1:04:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我就是这样，不知道为什么\N{\fs60}Because I am. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.94,1:04:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我不清楚艾娃知道多少...\N{\fs60}I didn't know how much Ava really knew...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.98,1:05:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}还是装做看不见\N{\fs60}and how much she ignored.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.17,1:05:03.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}她从不问我为何一个做运输业的\N{\fs60}She never questioned how a guy in the transport business
Dialogue: 0,1:05:03.98,1:05:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}能买得起18克拉的耳环\N{\fs60}could afford to give her 18 carat diamond earrings.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:07.15,1:05:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我想她也不希望知道答案\N{\fs60}I guess she didn't want to hear the answer.
