Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.08,1:05:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}和平谈判！\N{\fs60}Peace talks.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.86,1:05:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}好啦...算了...\N{\fs60}All right, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:46.87,1:05:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我转运到巴尔干半岛\N{\fs60}I'll re-route the shipment to the Balkans.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:48.48,1:05:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当他们说要打仗时\N{\fs60}When they talk about war,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.86,1:05:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}他们总是信守承诺的\N{\fs60}they keep their word.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:58.98,1:06:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}有了新一代的军火商\N{\fs60}Of course, a new breed of gunrunner
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.06,1:06:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}当然就要有新一代的警察\N{\fs60}requires a new breed of cop.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.89,1:06:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}亨利，走派克街\N{\fs60}Henry, take Park Avenue.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.10,1:06:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}带他们去新泽西逛逛\N{\fs60}Take 'em on a tour of New Jersey.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:04.37,1:07:08.57,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}尤里...有人朝我们的垃圾箱走来\N{\fs60}Yuri, there are men going through our garbage cans.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.82,1:07:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}大概是记者\N{\fs60}Well, it's probably just some reporters
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.82,1:07:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}找错人了吧\N{\fs60}looking for somebody else.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.10,1:07:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fs60}我总觉得他们不是小报的记者\N{\fs60}I have a feeling they don't work for the tabloids.
